<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Microsoft Script Editor'); ?>
        <p>The <strong>Microsoft Script Editor</strong> (<strong>MSE</strong> or "<code>MSE.EXE</code>" or "<code>mse7.exe</code>" in Office 2003) is an optional tool included in <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Office', 'ITS'); ?> 2000 through Office 2007 and is found in "<code>C:\Program Files\common files</code>" directory.</p>
        <p>It allows one to work with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTML', 'WD'); ?> code, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DHTML', 'WD'); ?> objects, and script in an Office document from within an Office application.</p>
        <p>In addition to this, if installed, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Internet Explorer', 'WB'); ?> will allow one to debug <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('JavaScript', 'L'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('VBScript', 'L'); ?> with the editor if the "Disable Script Debugging" Internet Explorer preference option is not checked.</p>
        <p>In the About Box, it calls itself "<em>Microsoft Development Environment 7.0</em>". It is a trimmed down version of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Visual Studio', 'IDE'); ?> .NET 2002 (7.0)'s IDE.</p>
